sentences: Ralph Earl Sutton (November 4, 1922 – December 30, 2001) was an American jazz pianist born in Hamburg, Missouri.
In 1956, he relocated to San Francisco, California, where he recorded several albums with Bob Scobey's dixieland band.
From the 1960s onward, he worked mostly on his own.
However, when the World's Greatest Jazz Band was established in 1968, he was the natural choice for piano.
He left that band in 1974 due to the extensive travel involved, and joined an old sidekick, Peanuts Hucko, in a quartet in Denver, near his home in Evergreen, Colorado.:
